This paper is about a new tracking algorithm that uses a deep neural network for matching. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves extensive training of the neural network, which suggests it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also evaluates its performance on video data, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking suggests it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) category.
